    <ContentPage.Content>
        <ScrollView>
            <StackLayout>
                <Label FontSize="Title" Text="Using Zvado Tools" VerticalOptions="Center"></Label>
                <Label>Note: when typing commands type them without the []</Label>
                <Label TextColor="Wheat" BackgroundColor="BlueViolet" FontSize="Title">What are zvado tools?</Label>
                <Label>Im zvado, I have made tools which allow you to sniff wifi networks for passwords. WE are going to look at my tools and built in kali linux tools. My tools are more lightweight and can be used both in kali and other linux distros.</Label>
                <Label TextColor="Wheat" BackgroundColor="BlueViolet" FontSize="Title">GIT</Label>
                <Label>Before we cotinue make sure you have git installed by opneing the terminal and typing [git --version] if you dont type [sudo apt install git]</Label>
                <Label TextColor="Wheat" BackgroundColor="BlueViolet" FontSize="Title">BH_konsol</Label>
                <Label>BH_konsol combines most tool in one command line intefrace. To install type [git clone https://github.com/viktor111/BH_konsol.git ] then cd in the installed file and type [pip install -r REQUREMENTS.txt
] if you dont have pip installed type [sudo apt install python-pip]
                </Label>
                <Label TextColor="Blue" BackgroundColor="Gold" FontSize="Title">Tools:</Label>
                <Label>Dont worry if things dont kae sense after the web/wifi basics guide evrything will make sense.</Label>
                <Label TextColor="Wheat" BackgroundColor="BlueViolet" FontSize="Title">mac-change</Label>
                <Label>Change your mac address just with a simple command whenever you want.</Label>
                <Label TextColor="Wheat" BackgroundColor="BlueViolet" FontSize="Title">net-scan</Label>
